dict.string: Navigate the file system with previews
Open navigation with the contents of configured folders
Pick a folder to start in

## Usage
Search for folders with the `nav` keyword and press <kbd>↩</kbd> to navigate the contents in a thumbnail view. Type to filter.
![Filtering for folders to search](images/about/navkeyword.png)
![Grid view of files](images/about/filegrid.png)
![Filtering for Catan](images/about/catanfilter.png)
* <kbd>↩</kbd> Open or preview file, or navigate inside folder. * <kbd>⌘</kbd><kbd>↩</kbd> Flip sort order. * <kbd>⌥</kbd><kbd>↩</kbd> Reveal in Finder. * <kbd>⇧</kbd><kbd>↩</kbd> Navigate to parent folder.
![Viewing a PDF](images/about/pdfview.png)
![Viewing Markdown file](images/about/mdview.png)
Alternatively, begin navigation in a folder via a [Universal Action](https://www.alfredapp.com/help/features/universal-actions/).
![Navigate with Universal Action](images/about/navua.png)
Configure the Fast Entry section in the [Workflow’s Configuration](https://www.alfredapp.com/help/workflows/user-configuration/) to start navigation with the contents of specified folders. Launch it via the `fnav` keyword or the [Hotkey](https://www.alfredapp.com/help/workflows/triggers/hotkey/).
![Keyword for Fast Entry Navigations](images/about/fnav.png)
Otherwise ↩ opens files in their default apps.
Launch with the contents of the chosen folder. Can take multiple paths separated by commas.
